# Patch: Bilevel / alternating MoE optimization (router vs expert phases)
#
# Problem:
#   moe-shaping studies a bilevel training procedure that alternates optimizer
#   updates between the MoE *router* params and the MoE *expert* params. Megatron
#   has native MoE but only a single, joint optimizer step. We need to (a) split
#   router and expert params into their own optimizer param groups and (b)
#   alternate which group actually moves, on a configurable cycle.
#
# What this patch does:
#   1. megatron/training/arguments.py (moe arg group): adds
#        --bilevel-router-steps  (router-only steps per cycle; 0 = disabled)
#        --bilevel-expert-steps  (expert-only steps per cycle)
#        --router-lr / --expert-lr (optional per-phase learning rates)
#   2. megatron/training/training.py, get_megatron_optimizer_config(): when
#      alternation OR per-group --router-lr/--expert-lr is set, adds 2 overrides
#      keyed by param name glob
#        ParamKey(name='*.router.*')  -> {'bilevel_role': 'router', [max_lr]}
#        ParamKey(name='*.experts.*') -> {'bilevel_role': 'expert', [max_lr]}
#      The custom 'bilevel_role' key makes each override tuple distinct, which
#      forces router and expert into separate param groups even when the LRs are
#      equal. ('*.experts.*' deliberately does NOT match '*.shared_experts.*'.)
#   3. megatron/training/training.py: module-level bilevel helpers + train_step()
#      hook. Right before optimizer.step(), the inactive role's param groups have
#      their lr masked to 0 (Adam update is lr * m_hat/(sqrt(v_hat)+eps), so lr=0
#      => no param change and no AdamW decoupled decay); lr is restored right
#      after the step and a module-level phase counter is advanced. The backbone
#      (attention/embeddings/norms/lm-head) trains every step.
#   4. megatron/training/training.py, training_log(): logs 'bilevel/phase'
#      (1 = router step, 0 = expert step) to TensorBoard and W&B.
#
# Caveats (acceptable for the current research milestone):
#   * The inactive group's Adam moments still update from their real grads; an
#     exact two-optimizer scheme would freeze the moments too.
#   * Global grad-norm clipping sees the inactive group's grads.
#   * Param groups split by 'bilevel_role' share the same checkpoint param-group
#     identifier keys (wd_mult, lr_mult, is_expert_parallel, is_decoupled_lr), so
#     resuming a bilevel run from a distributed checkpoint needs care. Checkpoint
#     saving is currently disabled on GH200 anyway.
#
# How to find the right location in a future Megatron version:
#   - args: search for the 'moe' argument group (parser.add_argument_group(
#     title="moe")) and the '--num-experts' argument.
#   - overrides: search for get_standard_config_overrides in
#     get_megatron_optimizer_config().
#   - mask: search for 'optimizer.step()' inside train_step().
#   - logging: search for "samples vs steps" in training_log().
#
# Applied to: Megatron-LM core_v0.16.1 (commit 55ac7082)
#
diff --git a/megatron/training/arguments.py b/megatron/training/arguments.py
